correctness.rationale: Major factual, structural, and schema issues are present. Key problems: (1) Top-level schema non-compliance: the output wraps a single process in a processes array, while the provided schema defines a single process object. (2) Multiple processes missing: the article reports three distinct IGZO ALD compositions (supercycles 0:2:2, 1:2:2, 2:2:2). Only one process is extracted; separate processes for Comp. A, B, and C are required. (3) Supercycle design incorrect: numberofSubcycles and subcycleSequence do not reflect the reported 0:2:2, 1:2:2, 2:2:2 ratios or per-oxide subcycles; ‘compound’ is given as InGaZnO instead of per-component oxides (In2O3, Ga2O3, ZnO). (4) Untraceable or fabricated parameters: pressure (10 mTorr), carrier/purging gas (N2), dosing/purge times, flow rates, nucleationPeriod, saturation, deliveryMethod, refractiveIndex, absorptionCoefficient, resistivity, carrierDensity, roughness, filmDensity, uniformity, conformality, onOffRatio are not reported in the article. (5) Schema violations: plasmaPower is set to null (must be an object if present); processParameters includes an extra filmThickness property not defined at that level (filmThickness belongs under thicknessControl). (6) Internal inconsistency: growthPerCycle 0.1 Å with 200 cycles implies ~2 nm, conflicting with the stated 20 nm film thickness. (7) Mislabeling/incorrect methods and units: optical band gap is taken as 3.1 eV but method is listed as UV-Vis; the article used REELS. materialProperties.electricalProperties.mobility is attributed to Hall measurements (not reported) and duplicates the device field-effect mobility. Device subthresholdSwing is set to 0.2 mV instead of 200 mV for 0.20 V/dec per Table 2, and the schema’s unit choice is mishandled. (8) Ambiguous composition: elementalConcentration is a single 14% value without specifying the element; although the Comp. C atomic ratio (1.0:0.7:1.5) matches Table 1, the concentration should identify each element. (9) Reactant selection partially correct but imprecise: O3 oxidant, TEIn, In–Ga bimetallic, and DEZn are correct, yet assigning all under compound=InGaZnO is semantically incorrect; they should be tied to their respective sub-oxides. (10) Some correct items (200 °C deposition temperature, 20 nm IGZO thickness, substrate SiO2/Si, device structure TGBC, μ_FE=36.9 cm2/(V·s), V_TH=−2.51 V) are present, but overall the extraction is largely unsupported by the text and breaches the schema. Properties to correct/review: top-level structure; add three processes; supercycleDesign a:b:c and sequence; remove/specify only parameters supported by the article; fix plasmaPower (omit if unused); correct SS to 200 mV; remove unreported electrical/optical/flow/time/pressure values; relocate/remove processParameters.filmThickness; avoid nulls; correctly assign band-gap method (REELS) and per-element compositions.

completeness.rationale: Major incompleteness and multiple schema/factual issues. (1) Missing processes: The article reports three distinct IGZO ALD compositions (Comp. A/B/C) using supercycle ratios 0:2:2, 1:2:2, 2:2:2 (TEIn:In-Ga:DEZn). Only one process is extracted, so the multi-experiment study is not represented. (2) Supercycle design not captured: numberofSubcycles and subcycleSequence are not encoded per sub-oxide/precursor (should list TEIn, In-Ga bimetallic, DEZn with counts 0/1/2, 2, 2, respectively). (3) Many parameters are untraceable to the article or fabricated: carrier/purging gas (N2), reactor pressure (10 mTorr), dosing/purge times (100 ms), flow rates, nucleation period, saturation, growth per cycle (0.1 Å), number of cycles (200), delivery method, uniformity (5%), conformality (AR=10), roughness (1.2 nm), density (5.5 g·dm−3), electrical resistivity and carrier density (and “Hall measurements”)—none are reported. (4) Internal inconsistency: GPC (0.1 Å/cycle) × 200 cycles contradicts the stated 20 nm film thickness. (5) Device properties partially incorrect: subthreshold swing is given as 0.2 mV, but the article reports ~0.20 V/dec (i.e., 200 mV/dec) for Dev. C (ITO); on/off ratio is not reported. (6) Film composition incomplete: only a single 14% value is provided; the article reports full at.% (In, Ga, Zn, O) and atomic ratios for each composition; these should be included (e.g., Comp. C In 14, Ga 9, Zn 21, O 56 at% and In:Ga:Zn = 1.0:0.7:1.5 via XPS). (7) Band gap method mismatched: article uses REELS; extraction states UV-Vis; only one band gap value (3.1 eV) is given despite three compositions with different E_G. (8) Schema issues: plasmaPower is set to null though the field type is object; if thermal ALD, omit the field. Overall, add three separate process entries (A/B/C) with correct supercycle counts, correct device metrics (e.g., μ_FE, V_TH, SS in proper units), and remove or justify parameters not supported by the text; fix GPC/cycle/thickness coherence; provide complete elemental compositions and REELS-derived band gaps for each composition.
